Title: President Durham Correspondence Regarding Martin Luther King, Jr. at Arizona State University
Description_y: Selected correspondence from volume 819 and volume 1113 of ASU President G. Homer Durham's papers regarding planning for and reaction to Dr. King's visit to ASU. Especially noteworthy is President Durham's June 4, 1964 letter to John G. Babbitt, President of the Arizona Board of Regents, providing details about how the event was organized and his perceptions of Dr. King's presentation. On June 9th, President Harvill of the University of Arizona wrote with a message of support and acknowledgement of King's previous appearances at that institution.
Preferred Citation: G. Homer Durham Papers, Office of the President Records, MSS-001 (ARCV), Arizona State University Library.
Parent Collection: Martin Luther King Jr. at Arizona State University
